info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Compute the Fosberg FWI fire danger index. Input measure is expected to follow the format:
- the time series is expressed in days;
- for each day there must be a group of 3 ordered values: temperature at noon (Â°C),relative humidity at noon (%),wind speed at noon (km h-1);
- all inputs must be of the same oph_type.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measures.
- index : name of the requested index.
					'RS' : rate of spread;
					'RSO' : zero wind rate of speed;
					'ER' : energy release;
					'EMC' : equilibrium moisture content;
					'FFWI' : Fosberg fire weather index (default).

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Compute the FFWI index from oph_doubles.
oph_fdi_ffwi('OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure)
